---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Blog - Gil Gatson"
  description="Insights on technology, geopolitics, business strategy, and entrepreneurship from Gil Gatson."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Blog</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Insights on technology, geopolitics, business strategy, and entrepreneurship.
    </p>
  </section>
  
  <div class="container">
    <div class="blog-grid">
      <article class="blog-card">
        <h2><a href="/blog/america-losing-ai-race">Why America Is Losing the AI Race to China</a></h2>
        <p class="meta">December 29, 2025</p>
        <p>
          In 2025, the AI contest is not about who drops the flashiest frontier model. It is about who can scale it, power it, staff it, and deploy it. China is winning the compounding game: open-weight distribution, electricity capacity, and coordinated deployment.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog/america-losing-ai-race" class="read-more">Read more ‚Üí</a>
      </article>
      
      <article class="blog-card">
        <h2><a href="/blog/energy-the-real-bottleneck-for-ai">The Unseen Handbrake: Why Energy, Not Talent, Is AI's Real Bottleneck</a></h2>
        <p class="meta">December 31, 2025</p>
        <p>
          Everyone's talking about algorithms and chips, but the brutal truth is that America's aging power grid is the single biggest threat to its AI dominance. Silicon Valley data centers sit empty for years waiting for power. China added 429 GW in 2024; the US added just 51 GW.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog/energy-the-real-bottleneck-for-ai" class="read-more">Read more ‚Üí</a>
      </article>
      
      <article class="blog-card">
        <h2><a href="/blog/the-open-source-trap">The Open Source Trap: How America Is Helping Its Rivals</a></h2>
        <p class="meta">December 31, 2025</p>
        <p>
          The well-intentioned push for open-source AI has become a strategic blunder, handing the CCP a playbook to accelerate its military capabilities. Here‚Äôs how it happened.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog/the-open-source-trap" class="read-more">Read more ‚Üí</a>
      </article>
    </div>
    
    <div class="coming-soon">
      <p>üìù Blog posts coming soon. Check back for regular updates on AI, geopolitics, and business strategy.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 4rem 2rem 5rem;
      margin: 0 0 4rem 0;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 50%, #0f3460 100%);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    
    .hero::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      bottom: 0;
      background: 
        radial-gradient(circle at 20% 50%, rgba(41, 128, 185, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 80% 80%, rgba(142, 68, 173, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    
    .hero h1 {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      color: #ffffff;
      font-size: 3rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .intro {
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
      text-align: center;
      color: #e0e0e0;
      margin-bottom: 0;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }
    
    .blog-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    
    .blog-card {
      padding: 2rem;
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
    }
    
    .blog-card:hover {
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    
    .blog-card h2 {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .blog-card h2 a {
      color: var(--color-text);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    
    .blog-card h2 a:hover {
      color: var(--color-accent);
    }
    
    .meta {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--color-gray);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    
    .read-more {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--color-accent);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    
    .read-more:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    
    .coming-soon {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: #f9fafb;
      border-radius: 8px;
      color: var(--color-gray);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
